</figure>
<figure id="CNX_UPhysics_39_05_bragg"><media id="fs-id1163712369539" alt="Figure shows the surface diffraction of a monochromatic electromagnetic wave on a crystalline lattice structure. The in-phase incident beams are reflected from atoms on the surface. Phi is the angle between the incident and the reflected beam, the in-plane distance between the atoms is a.">
